---
import DocsLayout from '../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';

const sidebar = [
	{
		title: 'Docs',
		links: [
			{ href: '/docs', label: 'Intro' }
		]
	},
	{
		title: 'PrismChart',
		collapsible: true,
		expanded: true,
		links: [
			{ href: '/docs/prismchart', label: 'Overview', active: true },
			{ href: '/docs/prismchart/installation', label: 'Installation' },
			{ href: '/docs/prismchart/foundation', label: 'Foundation' },
			{ href: '/docs/prismchart/chart-tools', label: 'Chart Tools' },
			{ href: '/docs/prismchart/development', label: 'Development' },
			{ href: '/docs/prismchart/credits', label: 'Credits' }
		]
	}
];

const toc = [
	{ href: '#overview', label: 'Overview' },
	{ href: '#features', label: 'Features' }
];
---

<DocsLayout title="PrismChart - Docs" sidebar={sidebar} toc={toc} issuesUrl="https://github.com/ether-strannik/PrismChart/issues">
	<style>
		.page-header {
			display: flex;
			gap: 1.5rem;
			align-items: center;
			margin-bottom: 2rem;
		}

		.page-icon {
			width: 64px;
			height: 64px;
		}

		h1 {
			font-size: 1.8rem;
			font-weight: 600;
			margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
		}

		.tagline {
			color: #666;
			margin-bottom: 0;
		}

		h2 {
			font-size: 1.2rem;
			font-weight: 600;
			margin: 2rem 0 1rem;
			padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
			border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e5e5;
		}

		.feature-list {
			list-style: none;
		}

		.feature-list li {
			padding: 0.4rem 0;
			color: #333;
		}

		.feature-list li::before {
			content: '[*]';
			color: #999;
			margin-right: 0.75rem;
			font-size: 0.85rem;
		}

		.feature-list strong {
			color: #000;
		}

		.btn-row {
			display: flex;
			gap: 1rem;
			margin-top: 2rem;
		}

		.btn {
			display: inline-block;
			padding: 0.6rem 1.2rem;
			font-size: 0.9rem;
			text-decoration: none;
			border-radius: 4px;
		}

		.btn-primary {
			background: #000;
			color: #fff;
		}

		.btn-primary:hover {
			background: #333;
			color: #fff;
		}

		.btn-secondary {
			border: 1px solid #e5e5e5;
			color: #666;
		}

		.btn-secondary:hover {
			color: #000;
		}

		.intro {
			margin-bottom: 2rem;
		}

		.intro p {
			color: #333;
			margin-bottom: 1rem;
		}

		.intro p.lead {
			font-size: 1.1rem;
			font-weight: 500;
			color: #000;
		}

		.intro hr {
			border: none;
			border-top: 1px solid #e5e5e5;
			margin: 2rem 0;
		}

		.comparison-table {
			width: 100%;
			border-collapse: collapse;
			margin: 1rem 0 1.5rem;
			font-size: 0.95rem;
		}

		.comparison-table th,
		.comparison-table td {
			text-align: left;
			padding: 0.75rem;
			border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e5e5;
		}

		.comparison-table th {
			font-weight: 600;
			background: #f9f9f9;
		}

		.comparison-table td:first-child {
			font-weight: 500;
			color: #000;
		}

		.workflow {
			background: #1a1a1a;
			color: #e5e5e5;
			padding: 1rem;
			border-radius: 6px;
			font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
			font-size: 0.9rem;
			margin: 1rem 0 1.5rem;
			overflow-x: auto;
		}

		.closing {
			font-style: italic;
			color: #666;
		}
	</style>

	<div class="page-header">
		<img src="/icons/prismchart.png" alt="PrismChart" class="page-icon" />
		<div>
			<h1>PrismChart</h1>
			<p class="tagline">Drawing and analysis platform for MetaTrader 5</p>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="intro" id="overview">
		<p class="lead">The complete trading workstation for MT5.</p>

		<p>Most traders juggle multiple apps: one for charting, one for journaling, one for screenshots, one for trade tracking, spreadsheets for statistics. Context scattered everywhere. Insights lost between tools.</p>

		<p>PrismChart brings it all together.</p>

		<hr />

		<p class="lead">One platform. Everything connected.</p>

		<table class="comparison-table">
			<tr>
				<th>What you need</th>
				<th>How PrismChart handles it</th>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td>Technical Analysis</td>
				<td>Layer-based drawing tools with visibility templates</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td>Time Context</td>
				<td>Sessions, news events, period separators - all as drawing objects</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td>Alerts</td>
				<td>Set on any drawing. Trigger captures screenshot automatically</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td>Trade Data</td>
				<td>MT5 positions flow directly into the journal</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td>Documentation</td>
				<td>Markdown notes attached to trades with screenshots</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td>Review</td>
				<td>Calendar view, filtered statistics, trade-by-trade analysis</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td>Portability</td>
				<td>Copy drawings across charts. Export and share setups</td>
			</tr>
		</table>

		<hr />

		<p class="lead">The workflow:</p>

		<pre class="workflow">Draw → Alert → Trade → Document → Review
                 ↓
          [all in one place]</pre>

		<p>Your analysis, your trades, your notes, your screenshots - connected. Not scattered across five apps hoping you remember to update each one.</p>

		<hr />

		<p class="lead">Not an indicator. A workstation.</p>

		<p class="closing">PrismChart treats chart analysis as a design discipline. Every element - separators, sessions, markups - is a drawing object in a layer. Organize them. Toggle visibility. Save templates for different views. Your chart, your system.</p>
	</div>

	<h2 id="features">Features</h2>
	<ul class="feature-list">
		<li><strong>Custom Price Scale</strong> Canvas-based rendering with rounded price levels</li>
		<li><strong>Custom Timeline</strong> TradingView-style with timezone support</li>
		<li><strong>Drawing Tools</strong> Lines, shapes, text, paths, position tool, Fibonacci</li>
		<li><strong>Layer System</strong> Organize objects by groups with visibility/lock controls</li>
		<li><strong>Alerts</strong> Price cross, zone entry, candle close alerts with notifications</li>
		<li><strong>Templates</strong> Save and apply drawing styles</li>
		<li><strong>Import/Export</strong> Share drawings across charts and terminals</li>
	</ul>

	<div class="btn-row">
		<a href="/docs/prismchart/installation" class="btn btn-primary">Installation</a>
		<a href="https://github.com/ether-strannik/PrismChart" class="btn btn-secondary" target="_blank">GitHub</a>
	</div>
</DocsLayout>
